worksforme: <p>
Hi, there are three parameters:
</p>
<ul><li>container: default is <em>div</em>, if it's empty <em>container_class</em> will not work
</li><li>container_class: class for the <em>container</em> parameter
</li><li>container_id: Not for the <em>container</em> parameter. It's for the list, example: <em>&lt;ul id="nav"&gt;</em>
</li></ul><p>
The HTML Output of:
<em>wp_nav_menu( array( 'menu' =&gt; 'top', 'sort_column' =&gt; 'menu_order', 'container_id' =&gt; 'nav', 'container_class' =&gt; 'menu-header' ) )</em><br />
is:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">&lt;div class="menu-header"&gt;
  &lt;ul class="menu" id="nav"&gt;
    &lt;li class="menu-item menu-item-type-custom" id="menu-item-10"&gt;
      &lt;a href="http://google.de"&gt;gg&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre><p>
Maybe you can update to the latest nightly and then check it again. If your problem still exists you can re-open.
</p>
